External knowledge: 
- The latest telemetry data refers to the most recent data point available for each vehicle, including speed, fuel consumption, battery consumption, and event type;
- The latest maintenance record includes the most recent maintenance date, type, description, cost, and the ID of the mechanic who performed the maintenance;
- The latest access log includes the most recent access date, access type, IP address, duration, and notes or comments about the access event;
- Vehicle details such as registration numbers, vehicle types, and current statuses are assumed to be up-to-date and accurate.
